    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>Wait, I might have misread your first part. You said \"the Client will not pursue you for damages,\" but then you said it \"shifts the risk to the consulting entity.\" Isn't indemnification actually the opposite? Like, wouldn't I be the one paying for their losses if I mess up? Can you clarify that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are correct that indemnification can be misunderstood. In this case, it's actually the opposite: the Client will not pursue you for damages, but that means you, the Consultant, will be held responsible for and pay for any losses or damages caused by your own actions. I should have rephrased my previous response: the Consultant (you) will bear the financial risk if things go wrong.",
